✨ HELLO 2023 ✨

Like clockwork… my word of the year is GRACE and/or ALIGNMENT 

That holds a special meaning to me and even made it Aevas middle name. I think the reasoning behind, I’ll keep to myself for now and save y’all time. It’s a long one 

Wow! Another year ey? I hope y’all gave yourself more GRACE this year. If not, friend I hope you give yourself GRACE for 2023. I left the fake it til you make it mentality, and gave myself GRACE to be ok not to be okay. I left the hustle mama mentality and gave myself GRACE to just be content with what I have. It’s ok to just be still for my sanity. I have enough under my roof. I know I will be blessed with exactly what I NEED and not I think I do. 

I did less travel planning overseas and planned more road trips. I learned to slow down and live for the day than always looking forward for tomorrow. My mentality is definitely shifting and realigning to focus more on what my soul needs. I learned to add boundaries because I learned that people can’t love the way I love and I can’t expect people to do what I do. That’s ok! I’m continuing to break generational cycles for my kids and with my life partner, my husband, we’re doing what we can to survive parenthood while not causing trauma. OUR KIDS ARE TOO MUCH 🤣 

Anyways! I wish you all peace and blessings in 2023! Be present, stay well, be kind, love one another! 🫶🏽 Hope you learn GRACE.. coz you’re enough! 

#newyearsameme #newyearalignment #newordoftheyear #graceisenough #graceyoureenough #lovemomlife #momtog #azmomlife #azcreatorcommunity #arizonacontentcreator #momblogger #momtogger #momphotographer #photographeraz #azlifestyle #azlifestylephotographer #newyearpost

🥶 Flagstaff 🥶

“Winters here”

My now desert raised kiddos were getting used to fake/bubble snow so we decided to let them experience the type of snow that mommy and daddy grew up in (MD/NY) A lot of people weren’t aware that it snows in AZ. Only 1.5-2 hrs north from us and we’re able to experience winter wonderland like we just did. We wouldn’t recommend going in the middle of a winter storm if you’re not used to driving in it. 

We were reminded how beautiful yet dangerous driving in the snow could be. It may have re-traumatized my husband 😂 and reminded us  one of the reason why we left the Virginia 😂 However, for the kids, guess we could say it was worth the treacherous drive. Little man liked it more than his sister but both had a blast playing in the snow. I was glad I kept some of my winter gears that has been collecting dust in our closet. 

We’re planning on going back. Maybe before the season ends but just not during a snowstorm 😂

Hope everyone is having a great start of the year!

We’ve always wanted to explore Tucson and we found the perfect time during Aevas 3 day break! Hubs drives here at times and we wanted to check it out coz he said it reminded him of some places of back home in DC.

🐶 puppy surprise 🐶

Most of you know that Aeva has been obsessing about owning a puppy someday. For years, every Birthday, every Christmas, all she asked for is a puppy. She got creative and started to draw our family portraits with her imaginary pet so much that her teacher started asking me how our nonexistent puppy was 😂 Her imagination is wild! 

We have been in contact with a breeder in the area and @cottonwood_ranch_yorkies because we planned on welcoming a yorkie. The breeder was amazing helping us for awhile now.

On Easter morning, got on the gram and a post popped up from another breeder I recently started following. Another local breeder in the state. I saw that there was two new puppies that were currently looking for a family. I inquired and the breeder contacted me and Lauren from  @yorkie_and_morkie_boutique was super helpful and amazing! Answered all my questions. Having known a few people who were scammed before, I had my guard up. However, Lauren made sure that I felt at ease. Prayed about it and I listened to my gut, and next thing you know, few days later, we were welcoming our fur baby. It actually went quicker than expected 😂 

We surprised Aeva when she got home! She was surprisingly SPEECHLESS! 😂 a new one for the books! For days she told us it still feels like a dream. 

Anyways… Everyone… say hi to “Bear” (naming him was a long process. We even thought about keeping the name the breeder gave him. He answered to “Bear” so I guess that’s the name he liked).

✨ let’s make Korean pancake ✨

Kimchi Pancake which is also called Kimchijeon and one of my favorite Korean dish. It’s normally served with rice. It’s super easy to make for a quick savory snack or appetizer. I love how easy it is to recreate at home because I know I crave it sometimes. I want to share how I make it in my house. 

Disclosure: I’m not Korean and by no means think mine is the best but this is how I make it at my house. 

I love Korean food and I love kimchi especially for its benefits and taste. Fermented foods can improve digestion, boost immunity, promote a healthy weight and more. 

Thank you @wildbrine for my gift package. We enjoyed every single one. Go check em out guys! @apexdropofficial 

Here’s what you need 

Kimchi @wildbrine 
1 cup Vegetable pancake mix (you can also just use flour) 
1 cup water 
Olive oil 
Your favorite soy based sauce

🫶🏽 Fathers Day shoutout 🫶🏽

How did you celebrate Father’s Day today?

I’m currently making him his fav Jamaican meals and letting him nap on the couch all day 😂 

I honestly don’t know what I did to deserve this man. He’s the most present Father, Daddy, Husband, friend, and sometimes my therapist 😂 Patient, loving, kind. 
15 yrs ago… I knew I made the right decision to give you my # 😂

I know we are all living in borrowed times and the older we get, it gets repetitive to celebrate these things year after year. As cliche as it sounds, every second we need to celebrate the people the in our lives. Celebrate your father if you’re blessed to still have one. Celebrate the life your father once had if they’re no longer with you in the present life. Celebrate the day you left that no good sperm donor. I am partnering with Ad Council and its public health partners to spread awareness about a topic dear to me. 

Did you know that 1 in 3 American adults has prediabetes? That's about 96 million! 8 out of 10 people with prediabetes don't even know they have it.

Know where you stand by taking the 1-minute prediabetes risk test at the link in my bio. If you are at high risk, don’t panic. The thing about prediabetes is it's often reversible, starting with some lifestyle changes. You should also talk to your doctor if you have any concerns.

Here's my story:

Both of my parents have diabetes. I had gestational diabetes when I had my last child, putting me at risk of developing type 2 diabetes. I knew I had to do something to prevent that from happening. I started making better health choices by tracking what I ate. I made it a habit to exercise daily. Even a 30 min walk is a great start.

Prediabetes is a warning sign from your body that indicates it's time to make some changes, and it's never too late to do so.

I encourage you to take the 1-minute prediabetes risk test through the link in my bio. We're in this together 🫶🏽

Truffle Pasta 

You’ll be surprised how easy this is! 

I ordered truffle pasta from one of the new restaurants we went to recently and I knew I wanted to recreate it at home. Thanks to @natureul.food for sending me this amazing truffle mushroom sauce. You can even put the sauce on a bruschetta or plain pasta. It’s def the best sauce I’ve had recently. It has the most amazing earthy truffle smell that I’m obsessed about. Anyways.. here’s the recipe and ingredients 

- @natureul.food truffle sauce
- pasta of your choice
- heavy cream
- 1 lb white mushroom 
- meatballs (optional)
- Parmesan cheese 
-olive oil
- salt/pepper 
- water 

- Bring water to boil add salt to water and Cook pasta for 10-12 min til Al dente. (4 quarts of water and 2 tablespoons of salt) Once cooked. Drain and set pasta aside 
- Place a large saute pan over medium heat, and add olive oil and mushroom. Cook for 2-4 minute until fragrant.
- Add heavy cream, and whisk. When bubbles form reduce the heat to very low heat. Add salt and pepper to taste. Whisk again.
- Add 1 cup of parmigiano cheese and 1-2 tbsp of @natureul.food truffle sauce or to your desired liking. Stir to combine. Turn the heat off. Add pasta 

Enjoy!

MY HOME 🏡 

It’s been a roller coaster ride since my dad’s diagnosis and one thing I know for sure is God has been with me through it all. He’s revealed things, answered things, and given me so much peace in this storm. All I needed was to BE STILL and let him orchestrate. 

My dad never had a chance to meet Des. I promised myself that I’ll never go back to see him on my own. Thankful that we were given the opportunity to go as a family. Seeing dad pushing himself to get up out of the hospital bed and refused help showed how much he wanted to see his grandkids.
